An elderly KZN farmer was found dead on his farm at Lions River, outside Howick, on Monday morning. According to the Midlands Emergency Service, their Howick Advanced life support paramedics crews were dispatched to Lions River. Midlands EMS spokesperson Roland Roberston said when they got there, a man was found dead lying in the yard tied up. Roberston said the man was declared dead at the scene by paramedics. “All local authorities were in attendance. The exact cause of the incident is under investigation by local authorities,” said Roberston. *A developing story